bonus /ˈbəʊnəs/

(bonuses) 

1. N-COUNT A bonus is an extra amount of money that is added to someone's pay, usually because they have worked very hard. 奖金 

例： Workers in big firms receive a substantial part of their pay in the form of bonuses and overtime. 大公司的工人，工资很大一部分是奖金和加班费。 

例： ...a $60 bonus. …一笔$60的奖金。 

2. N-COUNT A bonus is something good that you get in addition to something else, and which you would not usually expect. 额外收获 

例： We felt we might finish third. Any better would be a bonus. 我们觉得我们可能得第三名。任何更好的结果都是意外收获。

